President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed delight that Christians are extending gifts to Muslims. Buhari made the remark while commending the love shown between Christians and Muslims during the Ramadan period. He prayed that the Eid festival will continue to bring with it peace, safety, security, brotherhood and love amongst Muslims and Christians as witnessed during the fasting period. The president said this in his Eid-el-Fitr message issued by his spokesman, Malam Garba Shehu. “This model also shone through with Muslim groups joining Christian festivities. ”These are practices that promote brotherhood and forgiveness,” he said. Buhari also extended his best wishes to all Nigerians and Muslims across the globe.